gw.api.contact

Interface ContactRetireBean

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ContactContact, Message

    public interface ContactRetireBean
    This interface should be implemented by all entities that have non-safe foreign key properties on Contact, that need to check if their existence can prevent the retiring of the Contact. One example of this is ContactContact, as a contact can be related to a Contact which is cannot be retired, which therefore means this contact cannot be retired.

    If the entity implements this interface, the instance will have the computeCanRetireBeanForContactProperty() method called to check if this bean can be retired as part of retiring the contact. The implementation of the method should return true if this bean can be retired, false if not.

    • If the bean can be retired, any other beans in this bean's graph that should also be retired as part of retiring this bean should be added to the retireContext's beansToRetire list.
    • Before checking any beans in the entity the code should check the retireContext's visitedBean list to check if the beans have already been visited to avoid any potential loops in the graph, and add any visited beans to the same list.
    • If any beans need to be loaded for checking, they should be loaded through the Bundle contained in the retireContext.
    • If any other Contact entities need to be checked to see if they can be retired, use the ContactRetireHelper.computeCanRetireContact(Contact contact, ContactRetireContext retireContext) method to check that Contact.

    • Method Detail

      • computeCanRetireBeanForContactProperty

        boolean computeCanRetireBeanForContactProperty(IEntityPropertyInfo propertyInfo,
                                               Contact contact,
                                               ContactRetireContext retireContext)
        Returns true if this bean instance, which has a link to the contact parameter through the property parameter, can be retired. If it can be retired, the method will have added any other beans in the bean's graph that can also be retired to the retireContext's beansToRetire Set.
        Parameters:
        propertyInfo - the property which links the bean to the contact
        contact - the contact we're trying to retire
        retireContext - the context wrapper for the contact retire operation
        Returns:
        boolean indicates if the bean can be retired
